# Antinationals — environment example
#
# The Vite Supabase publishable configuration below is CLIENT-VISIBLE by
# design (VITE_ vars are inlined into the browser bundle). Row-Level
# Security in the database is what protects data — never the anon key.
#
# Server credentials must NEVER be committed or added to a VITE_ variable:
#   - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
#   - Google OAuth client secrets
#   - Cloudflare R2 access keys / secret keys
#   - Any signing key, worker token, or API key marked "secret"
# These are configured via the Lovable secrets tooling only and are
# available to edge functions at runtime.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL="https://<project>.supabase.co"
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=""
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=""

# Optional — canonical origin for <link rel="canonical"> and og:url.
# Leave unset until a permanent domain exists; SEO omits canonical entirely
# when this is not configured.
# VITE_CANONICAL_ORIGIN="https://antination.in"

# Optional — set to "true" only at the explicit launch step. When absent
# the site is served noindex,nofollow.
# VITE_ALLOW_INDEXING="true"
